nstable site from which to interrogate the politics of slavery. With focus on works by Josiah Wedgwood, Hiram Powers, Edmonia Lewis, John Bell, and Francesco Pezzicar, Beach uncovers both the radical possibilities and the conflicting limitations of art in the pursuit of justice in racial capitalism's wake.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520390102?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520390102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520390102/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY